Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium-fine red-brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 52, 6, 101a 31 or 206, 23. Perhaps from same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0373.09.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0505)
